{
  "texts": [
    "The two series have, as Lavin (2015, p. 621) notes, a \"plain[..] symmetry\" -except in so far as (E), since it already mentions something as a way of bringing about something else, must be broken up and reformulated.",
    "Now, in the series (E**)-(A) it is possible to put each item into the passive voice (e.g.",
    "'the arm is moved', etc.",
    "); and we might think that each passive construction corresponds to an event (the moving of the arm, etc.)",
    "placed within a causal network that includes a pathway from the arm's movements to a beneficial change in government via the deaths of the politicians."
  ]
}